===[[Pokémon Masters EX]]===
====Red====
{{main|Red (Masters)}}
Red, who is based on the [[player character]] from {{game|FireRed and LeafGreen|s}}, forms a [[sync pair]] with {{TP|Red|Charizard}}, {{p|Snorlax}}, {{TP|Red|Pikachu}}, {{p|Articuno}}, and {{p|Venusaur}} in [[Pokémon Masters EX]]. His Charizard is capable of [[Mega Evolution|Mega Evolving]] into Mega Charizard X and Sync {{Tera}}stallizing into the {{t|Dragon}} type, while his Snorlax and Pikachu are both capable of [[Gigantamax]]ing, and his Venusaur is capable of [[Dynamax]]ing. Red became a playable sync pair on February 28, 2020.

In this game, Red is indirectly responsible for the creation of the [[Pokémon Masters League]], as him defeating [[Lear]] before the events of the game was what inspired Lear to create [[Pasio]] and the PML in order to overcome his weaknesses. Red first appeared as an NPC during the second chapter of [[PML arc]]. He also made notable appearances later in the PML arc, and the [[villain arc]]. Unlike in Pokémon FireRed and LeafGreen, both Red and {{mas|Leaf}} coexist in this game.

